The topics change every year and   concern research fields. The lectures are given by top researchers in the field.
For this year there will be 3 winter schools 

* January 12 - 16 Complex networks. Responsible: Giovanni Neglia. [Detailed information about the content of this Winter School is available here.](http://www-sop.inria.fr/members/Giovanni.Neglia/complexnetworks15/)
* January 19 - 23 Verification and Computer proof. Responsible :Yves Bertot. [Detailed information about the content of this Winter School is available here.](https://team.inria.fr/marelle/en/coq-winter-school-2015-international-computer-science-master-university-of-nice/)
* January 26 - 30 Algorithmic Geometry of Triangulations. Responsible : Jean-Daniel Boissonnat. [Detailed information about the content of this Winter School is available here.](https://team.inria.fr/geometrica/winter-school/)

